<br>
When her drink arives she takes a deep gulp and sighs happily. She sets the cup on the table next to her chair ( not an easy feat ) taking care not to spill any on her light green robes. As she turns back around she notices a board with notes stuck all over it. She hops up to take a look. After a few minuites perusal she takes out a sheet of parchment, a well worn quill, and a small vial of ink from her hip bag. While scribbling her note she sticks her tongue out of the side of her mouth and concentrates. Finally she finishes it, pulls her wand out from where it was tucked in her belt, and levitates the note up onto the board and tacks it in place.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Howdy!<br>
<br>
I'm new to this adventuring life, thought I'd drop in and say howdy. My name is Kress Steelpin, but most everyone just calls me Spud. My brothers ( I got six of 'em! ) gave me that nick name as a baby and it just stuck. <br>
<br>
I'm a wizardess from Ak'anon, and I'm learning loads more each day! When I'm not out adventuring I like to read, do my research, race Gharabahldi ( that's my pet drogmor, more about him later ), and practice my aim on busted up tinkered contraptions. One day I might even tinker a bit myself!<br>
<br>
My whole family are warriors, all my older brothers and both my ma and pop. I never had much talent with a sword or a sheild, but when I was 6 I blew my brother Rupert's tinker-toy-horse into smithereenes! Bein' the only wizard in a family of warriors is tough, but I've learned to scrap along with the best of my relatives and after they see me cook a rat from 50 feet, well... they don't underestimate me! <br>
<br>
When I set off for adventure my brothers all chipped in and got me Gharabahldi, my drogmor. He's a fine red and white calico drogmor, and a real sweet heart, loves celery and skritches behind his horns. I just call him Ghari. <br>
<br>
Well, that's about it for now, my chocolate is getting cold. But if you ever see me around feel free to say howdy back!<br>
<br>
-Spud<br>
